<b>Lead Scoring</b> <p>

Algorithmic based profiling of leads in order to filter based on a set of predefined criteria.</p>
<p>

The practice is becoming increasingly popular in a world of web based server centric CRM software.</p>
<p>

An example of this would be generating a score for each client visiting a web site, or reading an email, to determine who is interested in a specific page or offer on a website, or email. The practice can be utilized effectively in delivering relevant content to a web visitor, increasing utility of the website or portal.</p>
<p>

The practice is also utilized extensively by Web Ad Serving companies who deliver web advertising based on a browsers previous behavior, or search engines who deliver sponsored ads based on previous searches.</p>
<p>

A whole new breed of web based software is being developed and introduced to the market place to enable sales and marketing organizations to make use of lead scoring, factoring in a smorgasbord of variables. Variables can range from human generated rank, to web generated analytics.</p>

